g.text: Kim Kitsuragi: "Remember," the lieutenant whispers. "He wants to tell us -- but he doesn't want to *help* us. It needs to look like we already have everything."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Ballistics. Let him cook here for a minute or two -- we can have another look at the set-up he had there, with the mattress." He nods southeast to the tower. "Ballistics always impresses these military types."
You: "Do you think he did it?"
You: "I'm trying to get him to confess..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I can see that, yes. I'm not judging."
Drama: Yes, sire! Make a production of this examination!
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good." He nods. "We're doing very good. He *wants* to confess -- I can see that. We just need to pile it on, a little more -- the more we have on him, the closer he is..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Remember," the lieutenant whispers. "He wants to tell us -- but he doesn't want to *help* us. It needs to look like we already have everything."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh yes..." He nods. "And -- he hasn't spoken to anybody in a long time. If we get him open, who knows what will pour out..."
Kim Kitsuragi: He smiles. "You should be proud. Come on -- let's wrap this up."

Kim Kitsuragi: "Ballistics. Let him cook here for a minute or two -- we can have another look around the island for a sniper's nest." He looks to the small tower on the coast. "I think we should check out the post."
Logic: You hear that? He thinks you're *this* close...
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. "From nothing to this in a day..." A crooked little smile. "This is *good*, we just need a confession first, and then *maybe* a solid motive later."
He nods. "From nothing to this in a day..." A crooked little smile. "This is *good*, lieutenant-yefreitor, we just need a confession first, and then *maybe* a solid motive later."
He nods. "From nothing to this in a day..." A crooked little smile. "This is *good*, Detective Du Bois, we just need a confession first, and then *maybe* a solid motive later."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Also, the gun." He smiles very politely. "We should pick it up and discuss it in front of him. Make a show of it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, good going -- that should be our *first* priority."
Suggestion: It doesn't have to hold in court. Just establish a line of sight and he'll do the rest himself.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well, I can think of one thing. The gun." He smiles very politely. "We should pick it up, and discuss it in front of him. Make a show of it."
You: "You think he has more? Than this case?"
You: "I'm slapping myself to get ideas!"
You: "How do you think the questioning is going?"
You: "What can I put on him -- to get him to fess up?"
Empathy: There is palpable excitement in his tone. He likes him for this -- *a lot*. But there's something more too...
You: Pat him on the back. [Leave.]
You: "What am I missing? What haven't I done?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "We just need to get him back to the mainland." A crooked little smile. "We actually did it..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "He's a communard. The victim was a mercenary. We should get him talking politics again. You could even tell him we already *have* a motive."
"He's a communard. The victim was a mercenary. From Oranje. If everything else fails, get him talking politics... You could even tell him we already *have* a motive."
Logic: He thinks the deserter has more than just this case in him. Forty-four years here...
You: "Let's get him back before we congratulate ourselves."
